	   <tr><td colspan=2>Welcome to Roshi’s rants, the week is my (belated) look at dungeon siege(beat it on Friday) and Freedom Force(almost done with it).<br><br>Well I played dungeon siege and beat dungeon siege, I never got to see the ending cause my computer froze every time I beat the boss. Well, how was the game? Very cool, very nice, but most of the bosses were god awfully easy, the final boss even was a piece of cake. The only boss that I had some kind of trouble beating was scorch the dragon (an optional boss at that). Other than that, it was an enjoyable, mindless dungeon hack. I think it plays like a cross between Diablo and Icewind Dale. I recommend it if you have not picked it up already.<br><br>Well, I have played through 95% of freedom force, I am on the last mission before the final boss. How is it? Amazing game. The superhero game curse has been lifted and we have a winner. I am sure you have heard enough about it so I will say no more, except that a few of the heroes (Man-Bot, Sea Urchin and The Ant) were completely useless, other than that, the game is great.<br><br>On last thing in the ongoing Div3 fiasco, I had the leader of div3 call me an a-hole online after I went on a public forum and basically said the guild was not so great. What I find so funny about this is that man has such a high opinion of his guild he fails to see any problems with it. Hey that’s life, I have fallen for that(on this journal) but you need to take criticism to be successful. He was mainly mad that I did not sign my name, but I had my screen name as an identity and frankly so what. When I flared up at Mr. Anon awhile back, I got mad that he did not even have a screen name, but just an anonymous. Its ok not to sign your name as long as you have some name I can call you. <br><br>Nortsrum, if your reading this, this is Redtaped telling you to get a life, there are bigger fish to fry, your guild is not perfect, no ones guild ever is. <br>Roshi out.&nbsp;&nbsp;  <br>