	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi, I have not posted in two weeks due to various problems in RL, but I am back.<br><br>I am looking forward to two games, Dungeon Siege and Morrowinds, two dungeon-hack RPGS. I think these will games will rock but I do NOT want those #*$_^ random dungeons. I HATE random dungeons. Why? Because ,A) I get seriously lost without a map and B) they throw all suspension of disbelief into the wind. I will use two examples. First is Diablo II which I am assuming will be similar to dungeon siege. They had random dungeons. Now this was fine for sewers and hell, but for Harems and Monestaries? You have got to be kidding. No wonder those girls were slaughtered by the legions of hell, they could not find the exit. I am sure they even got lost looking for the bathroom. Daggerfall was just as bad, with dungeons called ”The ruins of the &lt;insert random family name here&gt; Estates”, you would think that you would be fighting in a house. Nope, they should have been called “The ruins of the CITY of &lt;insert random family name here&gt;”. Now AO has random dungeons, but they exist in RANDOM missions, not predetermined areas. I just hope either of these two game don’t have random dungeons, cause I will run from the game in frustration.<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;           Roshi out.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
