<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101560920081892></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101560920081892><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=101560920081892>cycle</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=101560920081892#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=91720><span id= >roshi the Charming</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>119 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 8th 12:41 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi this week I talk about my faviorate topic I have never talked about, “The Fanboy Cycle”.<br><br>What is the fanboy cycle, well I am sure you have seem it many times, its happened with AO, DAOC and now with the new crop of MMORPGS namely SW:G and SB. <br><br>1.New MMORPG is announced.<br><br>2.People get all excited about and jump on any piece of info.<br><br>3.People go to current MMORPG boards and scream how the game will rule and kill the MMORPG the current board is about.<br><br>4.Game goes into beta; Fanboys don’t beta test but skew any negative info into a postive light.<br><br>5.Game goes into release.<br><br>6.Fanboy finds out game is not as good as the though it was and gets mad.<br><br>7.They bitch on the game boards about how the developers are evil and the game sucks.<br><br>8.Fanboy cancels accounts and tells everyone about it.<br><br>9.Repeat ad Infinitum. <br><br>Yes, you have all seen this cycle many times, most noticeably with DAOC. DAOC was supposed to be the EQ-killer, when it wasn’t they all got mad and felt betrayed. I can see this. Can the cycle be broken? I think so. First MMORPGs need to have more of the game finished upon release and have it stable as well. Then the fanboys need to understand that the current MMORPGs are not going anywhere. AO and DAOC are not dying nor will they in the near future. UO, AC and EQ are still going strong even competitors. SB AC2 and SW:G will be decent(okay not so much SW:G but it will be fair, I have already talked about it) but they will in no way be the holy grail of MMORPG gaming, they will have problems and they fanboys will need to realize no game will ever be perfect, not even Warcraft 3 and Neverwinter Nights. In the end, it all comes to hurt feelings on the part of that Fanboys, so next time don’t get all so excited about game, because you felling might get hurt and then the vicious cycle will repeat itself.<br> Roshi out.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
