<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101529334150324></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101529334150324><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=101529334150324>RE: greatness</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=101529334150324#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=91720><span id= >roshi the Charming</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>119 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 4th 8:57 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok well its not Friday, but I don’t want to waist a valuable Friday on Progress Quest so there are two rants this weeks and this makes up for the week I missed (like anyone cares except me).<br><br>Progress Quest is a massively popular MMORPG where the sole point is to get uber. In fact you have NO control over you character at all. You just sit there and watch little bars and numbers expand. No graphics, no sound, just a character sheet with your stat and inventory and a little line at the bottom of the screen telling you what your avatar is doing; killing, running quests, buying equipment ect.. Nay Sayers point out that this is a stupid game because there is no game, but they fail to see the point. The game and its accompanying forums (found on the website) are a stinging satire of MMORPGs. Why? Because when you strip down the graphics, the sound and all the bells and whistles from every MMORPG out there, you get PQ. Sure UO has a skill based system (I will get to the myth of the skill-based system superiority soon) and AO maybe in the future but you doing essentially what you’re doing in PQ. Your just “going to the killing fields” and slaying creatures to get equipment and xp. Sure the killing fields may change, it could be a dungeon, a forest or an icy plain, but they are still killing fields. You may be wielding an axe or a really big gun, but they all serve the same purpose, to kill things.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the end no matter what game your playing, it all comes down your stat sheet of an imaginary character, however in PQ, that is all there is.   <br><br>The official PQ forums also require some mention. Those forum simulate the average forum for most MMORPGS. There is a trading board, a tech board and a Developer board that is in Latin. If you scroll down the posts you begin to realize that there is every type of issue being made fun of: nerfs, patches, D00D, guilds, tech problems, you name it, its probably there. However, the most important piece of satire there is the developer board.  Today most developers seem to be isolated from their users. They seem to be in their own little world and do things at their whim. The communications problems are so bad it’s as if the developers are speaking Latin because they don’t seem to understand the players and vice versa. <br><br>In the end, PQ is so popular because it is so true on so many levels. I hope that developers take a long hard look at the issues PQ implies and attempt to improve their products and I don’t mean be like PQ.<br>Roshi out.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
