	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hope everyone’s Valentines Day went well, mine was good. This week’s rant is an older one that I wrote but never put up due to EQ legends being announced. This may be slightly out of date but the point still is the same today as it was when I wrote it.<br><br><br>For several months now, I have been following what people are saying about EQ, DAOC and AO on message boards. As far as EQ, things have cooled down from the flame fests that EQ message boards were a few months ago. AO is somewhere in the middle between flame fests and general chatting. But it’s the DAOC boards I want to talk about, specifically this one:&nbsp;&nbsp;  <br><br><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5176" target=_new>http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5176</a><br><br>As you can see from the link, this is the developer’s board for DAOC on ign.com. Why am I talking about this? To make a point, of course. If you look at most of the posts on the list you many of them are about the same topic and almost none of them are of any use to the developers because players just whine and whine and whine on those boards. No I whine about this and that too but I have toned down quite a bit since October, but even them I tried to make my point as concise and level headed as possible (there are few notable exceptions of course). Also, if you’ve been watching the boards, you’ll notice almost no developer presence on the boards, which is mostly Sanya Thomas( aka. Tweety, who wrote on Lum the Mad before she was “bought out”). AO has more presence than that on most AO boards and it can be argued that they had it worse.<br><br>But why isn’t she there now, three reasons. First, there is so much whining on the boards, it is hard to keep a post on the board for more than five minutes, so its hard to keep track of things. Second, there is Camelothearald.com where Mythic keeps players in touch with what is happening; but without message boards, because of reason number two. Starting about December, when the real state of DAOC came out, Sanya got flamed and even a number of times, got death threats. Why should she post when she gets death threats if she does. She is there to help you, not be your enemy; but if you act like that why should she care. Verant shut down their message boards because of the same behavior.  However, she says it best herself at <br><br><a href="http://tweety.bowlofmice.com/tweety/" target=_new>http://tweety.bowlofmice.com/tweety/</a><br><br>One could blame Mythic’s behavior as just being mean when it comes to communication because they turned into Verant, but remember that Verant has to deal with the same crap as Mythic does.  Therefore Mythic got tired of dealing with rabid dogs that would jump at you at any chance and wised up, like Verant. Sure Mythic’ behavior seems mean, but with what they have to deal with, do you blame them. If you got flamed twenty-four seven, would you make yourself a target? I wouldn’t and neither do they. No game company is willing to put up with that. They want levelheaded discussions, not a no-holds-barred match. So next time you venture over to those boards, ask yourself, who caused the communications problem, is it Mythic or did the players fail to remember history and just brought it on themselves? <br>Roshi out.<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Feb 15 13:09:25 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
