	   <tr><td colspan=2>I had a rant for this week about DAOC, but Verant had to go and do something dumb again. Therefore EQ bashing has started again, for this week anyway.<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp; Everquest Legends has left me breathless, now the stuff they are offering, is somewhat good stuff, no doubt about it; but the way they are offering it, is what I am here to rant about. The service, if you have never heard of it, is that you pay 40$ a month for services listed here in descending order of usefulness: Interactive maps (which zone your in, bound in, have been in ect. This is a good idea because EQ is huge), Guild pages (Most guilds have pages, but its good to have them in one spot and the features are cool), character pages (good idea, but was improved from an idea started by FC), Dynamic server and calander of events (server with more GM events and a calendar to keep track of events, there should have been more gm events all along but the calendar is useful), legendary items (nothing more than a chance for you to get more uber) and story pages (zzzzzz…….).<br><br>	The stuff they are offering is mostly good, but would you pay 40 bucks and why here and why now. Verant is out to make money, as usual, and this is nothing but a ploy to make money. But what makes this a “Cheesy Tactic”(A money making ploy so obvious, its almost seem cheesy or stupid) is that Verant is obviously doing this to squeeze out as much money as they can for a slowly dying game. I don’t play EQ anymore but I do know the EQ’s player base has to be shrinking. This service however, comes a little to late and just illustrates a point I have made many times. Verant by enacting this service, fails to mention that the underlying problems in the game, downtime, the uber mentality and the economy, are still there. Sure, having dynamic game play is cool, but have fun would it be by some uber-guild and D00Ds ruining it for everyone. Sure you can go dungeon crawling with a purpose, by why would want to spend eight hours doing it. People aren’t leaving because of no dynamic maps, their leaving because of fundamental problems and competition who promises to do things better.<br> I have to give props to Verant for the quality of the services; but they are nothing more than an excuse to shell out more money for obviously desperate company. Maybe if they were only an extra 10 bucks a month or for that much downtime is also reduced, I would not be here complaining, but it is. People will buy it, no doubt; but its nothing more then a chance to extend the life for slowing dying game.<br>Roshi out.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
