<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100981560483919></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100981560483919><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=100981560483919>Year end</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=100981560483919#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=91720><span id= >roshi the Charming</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>119 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 31st 11:20 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.48]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Welcome to the year-end edition of Roshi’s rants, where I talk about future and current MMO games. I am only going to say my thoughts on the idea and not go so much into reviews of games I have never played.<br><br><br>Some Future games:<br>Big World: AO clone enough said, will give AO a run for its money if it is any good. Its about time we start seeing more futuristic games. However there is no talk of a beta test and their site has not been updated in a month so I wonder if its going to be released in the near future.<br> <br>City of Heroes: Great idea for a game. I look forward to being able to play as a super hero. I might sign up for beta testing. There is one problem I can foresee in the game, one that plagues many game; the unbalancing of powers. For example, fire is way more power than lightning and the ice power is useless, but hopefully the game will ship balanced.<br><br>Earth and Beyond: The name of this spaceship combat game is also shared by a now dead space combat TV series. Lets just hope that the game does not have the TV show’s quality, which was bad.<br><br>E.VE: “EVE: The Second Genesis, is a massively multiplayer, online, persistent world game. perhaps even too real to be called a game.” This quote of their site says it all in my opinion. This game is like Earth and Beyond and Jumpgate. I believe this game will blow up in space if the hook is, “its more than a game”.<br><br>“Gundam” MMO: Well Gundam is a mech series of games, series and toys based in Japan. I have nothing against it, but I wouldn’t play it.<br> <br>Horizons: This in nothing but vaporware.<br><br>Lost Continents: You in an Indiana Jones type world complete with huge private worlds. I call this a winner if the developers live up to their promises. However the game seems rather early in development so we will have to wait and see.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Shadow Bane: Ahh! Yes, the much proclaim DOAC killer. The is a total PVP game set in a fantasy universe. I think it will do fine, but since I am not into PVP that much I will not play it.<br><br>Star Wars: Galaxies: I have already talked about this game so I will not talk about it here. You can find it under the heading “The fleecing of Star Wars”.<br><br>Current Games(the “big ones”):<br>EQ, DAOC and AO: I have talked enough about these so I will not talk about them.<br><br>WWII Online: This WWII simulator is pretty much dead in the water because Playnet, the host of it, filed for chapter 11 bankruptcy. This game failed because it was release way too soon for its own good. If it was released when it was done, it could have been great.<br><br>Jump Gate  and Motor City Online: These 2 games are genre defining game, meaning that they are really the first in their class of MMOGs. Any game in these genres(Jump Gate is most defining because of EVE and E.A.B) will simply build  off of what these games paved they wave for. These games are not overly good but defining. WWII Online is also defining but its too bad to be defining in any sort of way.<br><br>AC: Never mentioned this game before, but if you want to know the truth, this game was only released because of Microsoft’s big ego, “We’re Microsoft, lets make an EQ clone and try to kill it.” Well AC is doing all right but not as well as EQ.<br><br>UO: Is this game still alive?<br><br>Lineage: Heard this game is not very good but its big in Korea<br><br>Roshi’s awards:<br><br>Most likely to dominate in the future: SW:G,  because its Star Wars and the mindless Star Wars fans and most everyone else will flock to it even if its crap.<br><br>Best of Year market wise (not quality because I have only played 3 of the 8 games):  Though call, but it will have to go to Linage because it has over a MILLION subscribers. However, just because it has that many subscribers does not mean I will touch it with a ten-foot pole.<br><br>Most disappointing:<br>WWII Online: Could have been great but it was too rushed and not advertised enough, so it sucked, sad to see it go, but it will.<br><br>Single player game of the Year(I have played most of the good games this year): <br>This will have to go to Max Payne. Max Payne is the coolest game ever released. From the great storyline to the game play, this game blew me away, go pick it up, its cool.<br><br>Well this concludes this rant and have a happy new year!<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
